=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Protect commercially available 2-isopropylphenol as the methyl ether (e.g., MeI/K2CO3 or Me2SO4/base) to give 2-isopropylanisole. | Step 2: Directed ortho-lithiation of 2-isopropylanisole at the remaining ortho position with s-BuLi/TMEDA (low T) gives 6-lithio-2-isopropylanisole. | Step 3: Add cyclobutyl methyl ketone to this aryllithium to form the tertiary benzylic alcohol intermediate 2-isopropyl-6-[C(OH)(CH3)(cyclobutyl)]anisole. | Step 4: Deoxygenate the tertiary alcohol (e.g., Et3SiH/BF3·Et2O or equivalent benzylic tertiary alcohol deoxygenation) to give 2-isopropyl-6-(1-cyclobutylethyl)anisole. | Step 5: Demethylate the anisole with BBr3 to furnish the exact target 2-isopropyl-6-(1-cyclobutylethyl)phenol, CC(C)c1cccc(C(C)C2CCC2)c1O.

